ype\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Investigating image metadata issues**\\\\n\\\\nI've come across a potential issue with the native image reflection metadata from tests. If the reflection metadata is missing, those tests may fail until the agent generates it. I wonder if the external workflow first runs the agent. In this repo, it seems like nativeTest uses metadata files from the metadata folder, but not generated ones? I need to dig deeper to understand this situation better.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Implemented coverage-focused tests for `org.codehaus.plexus.util.reflection.Reflector`.\\n\\nChanged files:\\n- `tests/src/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-utils/1.0.4/src/test/java/org_codehaus_plexus/plexus_utils/ReflectorTest.java`\\n  - Added dedicated public `ReflectorTest`.\\n  - Covers:\\n    - public constructor lookup and `Constructor#newInstance`\\n    - public instance field lookup/read\\n    - public static field lookup/read\\n    - public instance method lookup/invoke\\n    - public static method lookup/invoke\\n    - singleton factory lookup/invoke\\n    - legacy `getObjectProperty` failure path\\n- `tests/src/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-utils/1.0.4/src/test/java/org_codehaus_plexus/plexus_utils/Plexus_utilsTest.java`\\n  - Made the existing top-level test class public to comply with the test-class rule.\\n\\nI did not compile or run tests, per your instruction. Note: there was an unrelated untracked `metadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-utils/1.0.4/` path already present; I left it untouched.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0bb7e750437af3830169f4f55cbc88819db514785731bb9433\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 311, \"output\": 1773, \"cacheRead\": 25088, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 27172, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReas