r to understand this situation better.\\\\\\\"}]}\\\"}, {\\\"type\\\": \\\"text\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"Implemented coverage-focused tests for `org.codehaus.plexus.util.reflection.Reflector`.\\\\n\\\\nChanged files:\\\\n- `tests/src/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-utils/1.0.4/src/test/java/org_codehaus_plexus/plexus_utils/ReflectorTest.java`\\\\n  - Added dedicated public `ReflectorTest`.\\\\n  - Covers:\\\\n    - public constructor lookup and `Constructor#newInstance`\\\\n    - public instance field lookup/read\\\\n    - public static field lookup/read\\\\n    - public instance method lookup/invoke\\\\n    - public static method lookup/invoke\\\\n    - singleton factory lookup/invoke\\\\n    - legacy `getObjectProperty` failure path\\\\n- `tests/src/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-utils/1.0.4/src/test/java/org_codehaus_plexus/plexus_utils/Plexus_utilsTest.java`\\\\n  - Made the existing top-level test class public to comply with the test-class rule.\\\\n\\\\nI did not compile or run tests, per your instruction. Note: there was an unrelated untracked `metadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-utils/1.0.4/` path already present; I left it untouched.\\\", \\\"textSignature\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"v\\\\\\\":1,\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"msg_0bb7e750437af3830169f4f55cbc88819db514785731bb9433\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"phase\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"final_answer\\\\\\\"}\\\"}], \\\"api\\\": \\\"openai-responses\\\", \\\"provider\\\": \\\"OCA\\\", \\\"model\\\": \\\"gpt-5.5\\\", \\\"usage\\\": {\\\"input\\\": 311, \\\"output\\\": 1773, \\\"cacheRead\\\": 25088, \\\"cacheWrite\\\": 0, \\\"totalTokens\\\": 27172, \\\"cost\\\": {\\\"input\\\": 0, \\\"output\\\": 0, \\\"cacheRead\\\": 0, \\\"cacheWrite\\\": 0, \\\"total\\\": 0}}, \\\"stopReason\\\": \\\"stop\\\", \\\"timestamp\\\": 1777661255325, \\\"responseId\\\": \\\"resp_0bb7e750437af3830169f4f547ca28819db2827cef4b1b85ec\\\"}}\\n1908:[recv] {\\\"type\\\": \\\"turn_end\\\", \\\"message\\\": {\\\"role\\\": \\\"assistant\\\", \\\"content\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"thinking\\\", \\\"thinking\\\": \\\"**Investigating image metadata issues**\\\\n\\\\nI've come across a potential issue with the native image reflection metadata from tests. If the reflection metadata is missing, those tests may fail until the agent generates it. I wonder if the external workflow first runs the agent. In this repo, it seems like nativeTest uses metadata files from the metadata folder, but not generated ones? I need to dig deeper to understand this situation better.\\\", \\\"thinkingSignature\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"rs_0bb7e750437af3830169f4f5487534819d82fe25a897bc799a\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"reasoning\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"encrypted_content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"gAAAAABp9PVcmt11-xVYDUd5jAUpIMwdjCzdGPShWhJu00MYLhliuhV41qXVNiYiN0-rr-R5nDxp5zYRWx5eBd2qBl0jf-afM4sLN7DDkoSyXBxBiiLyAHb-IOknnA3lEjIQGyMqTInBNKpPp2Z5wbay5ieLj-8PmCKV0n_a3wpCh_W58Uru1EwZmbT5vjzBWmCiWZZQn2p_e9ZvqHqnijA6oHTyid3wVKzxrh-vwwdQ9QYdp3349fafXQHZ3yZb9m9_l8eURYUHmRkApfLUPRUhePwqZ8xyjNpxs2MgTSrGiBgAPJsPeJ11qoyyt-tU_IbOdOxG-HQJYqeiCTDbRFV03Xq6Ov3BiVn1UQDS0iTYGp0Kuft9de1igNhb6KjJnhpbTf_41b-D9KIzq94XHZkaux3OPj0aVj-1SDyS_Ktdp-_3FFnGGb67Uq0tKNeI3F4WutYun5LeX2P6pDG3R6584g9YKHS6ddtP-7tnfZxU3xIEwfCmfPhs4Clnxg3FYnoh6xWjw28lpRsRKy02LncxHiEMYWK4FNFaZ7HwtMHvGZomSlMF4-Lmb8-LOlaPRW-Qc6EYS2IKyUSg3ZWydIrzw_RH0_zsaJmS0hKekvjl_jHTs8kNG7Mh5eFkWMuCXeh1hDVln5Rhs9cdFfvmxpbzSqfKTinmQSoxrjISkQM8grBhDkhBgN6bCEgdt43bRvyQuuizOYg55vmJv2M3hmdIFIQjNDTNUPFF-WtzkbGfa7Jz7xGfj2xzvfkmBEtHdhbnHfxg8380FTHa3HXB34fLrRKyHaB9--xS_F2x7lcVcrrT8wTq8cWsH01i4blfUcNS-IB-Adm32_J9-BYG389fUdk-JEu6snVlOURLNJKyPONo0y5NMjxlcC0dCdjEPijNhUEQzsca0eCozvOszYU7ShFtHou6dYS4vRbVfAmC_n3bb7Z0JM0HSjVkSMVjth9LLr1GiMYYlMBca5TeQ9RbCizvqEG01EFqBV_WmI9L04XMsMZR0yN7p2EBiT3574jyYDxbrENhhM1yJOfKGd_XzJZk9BW3HTS1gJ_PiSkHP_zZzlB2HU2y3XH4s8OCI2dURxpsKBlRTfLUn1UaJ-0P40QZ0PxmI0MIy9QThnqQLVjW56YF_Xe4PZEJsdqINh-EcXUwj9nv58yFSzD5VmnnjzJ-w1H-GTz4WkLd3YeExQbghc88oZhrjyQLUCqKvPcddJNtUOJp5-xqm5rCu1dEj3lTZCXbsdICgrmQYIGBVYz7QzqKQxpufnjEIMpyDa1TG4snLef6NIyD__ugSe2